<normalizedToken id="9FA7C96E652909DC8AD218600A23A57C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(1.1 
<normalizedToken id="23C88DC1EE2DFB3F0B46FAF86644C897" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
) as long as length of mesosoma. Petiole longer than wide in dorsal view. Gaster ovate, 2.2-2.4 
<normalizedToken id="5EA3429D28244D27A25580E777E909F8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(2.3 
<normalizedToken id="C6247D182C2831D4C267BBCCE78BB638" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
) as long as wide. Ovipositor exserted beyond apex of gaster.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8470A144834F470030D2412D628F0399" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="3C88C2CDBF5C738B14237D3A92F70B67" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Male</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1CC0A7D89A8761FFEB27BA12B2BA82D2" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 3. Hemiptarsenus tianshuiensis sp. nov., female, holotype (1, 2), male, paratype (3) 1 habitus in dorsal view 2 habitus in lateral view 3 habitus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 100 μm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.85228.figures1-3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/688634" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">3</figureCitation>
